 were at ( gnomes are not used to being at such high altitudes), and beckoned his wife to look down.  The woman put down the child, and rm in arm, they stared at the ground and at the trees.<br><br>They were a bit too close to the edge.  The man fell first, he tried to let go of his newlywed bride but she held on trying to bring him up, alas she pulled herself down.<br><br>The child was abandoned.  He had no family.  He had no ties back in Ak`anon, not to mention no way to GET back to Ak`anon.  He meandered around Kelethin, careful to not fall off and suffer the same fate as his mother and father.<br><br>He wandered into a building.  Inside this building elves were practicing nature magick.  He watched as one elf's skin sprouted thorns.  Another became a wolf.  Yet another made himself disappear.  One even conjured a swarm of insects, and then dismissed it.<br><br>He was approached by one of these druids, she came up to him and asked about who he was, how he got there, and where his parents were.  Sadly this gnome was too young to talk.  The druid told him to stay put as she ran away.<br><br>The horns of Kelethin sounded.  Everyone in the town gathered to see what was the matter.  The druid brought the gnome child up to the town's announcement stage.  She asked the city if anyone knew anything about the parents of this child. <br><br>No one responded.<br><br>They waited.<br><br>And waited.<br><br>And a party of adventurers came, and announced that they had found the remains of two adult gnomes at the bottom of the city, they were dead, unable to be saved.<br><br>The druid, and everyone else in the city, put two and two together.<br><br>The merciful druid decided to take the young gnome in for the time being.<br><br>She brought him with her to her druid classes at her training guild, as he had no one else to watch over him.  During one of the training sessions, the young gnome got distracted playing with one druid's summoned bear.  The head of the druid guild brought the kindly druid aside, and wispered what seemed like important matters into her ear.<br><br>________________________________________________<br>MEANWHILE<br>( in a cave off steamfont mountains )<br>________________________________________________<br><br><br>A most evil gnome, shrouded in death itself, storms through the halls, past minotaurs, followed by two henchmen, in a most hurried fashion.<br><br>&quot;How did you ever let this happen?!?  You let one of our own get taken in by the forces of Tunare?&quot; The leading gnome shouted.<br><br>&quot;But Meldrath, we couldnt have just snatched him up, and we certainly couldnt create a conflict there, in the house of Tunare&quot;  The first crony said.<br><br>&quot;And he isn't ours yet, just because you think you can &quot;forsee&quot; important necromantic powers in someone doesn't mean they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  belong</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to you, he has to choose to follow necromancy,&quot; the second one chimed in.<br><br>&quot;I will have him, you can bet on that.  He has exceptional powers.  I will not let such a gem idle.  He would make a great asset to the plague.&quot; Meldreth said.<br><br>&quot;The time is coming.  We need to gather our resources.  This fledgling is essential to our goal.  Bertoxullous be praised, the Karanas will flow with ichor like a tidal wave.&quot;<br><br><br>PART 2 COMING SOON <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uickhorvonmemnoch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ickhor Von Memnoch</A> at: 7/9/02 11:24:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urobynswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RobynSwiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 434<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/10/02 4:08:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.show